# Amari
My name is amari . I am from Houma Louisiana. I went to Covent Christian academy high school. My major is business administration, i am currently a sophomore at Ul. 
- **Favorite color**: Blue
- **Pet**: None
- **Super Bowl prediction**: Chiefs will win
import nltk
from nltk.corpus import gutenberg
import string

# Load the text
file_id = 'dickens.txt'
text = gutenberg.raw(file_id)

# Tokenize the text
tokens = nltk.word_tokenize(text)

# Remove punctuation and count words
words_no_punctuation = [word for word in tokens if word.isalpha()]
word_count = len(words_no_punctuation)

print(f"Total words (no punctuation): {word_count}")
# For advanced counting, you can use a frequency distribution
from nltk import FreqDist

fdist = FreqDist(words_no_punctuation)
fdist.plot(30, cumulative=False)  # Plot the 30 most common words
